  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scholarships for Afghan Women and Girls</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">More Afghan women and girls are graduating from high school and going on to university to become teachers, engineers, doctors, administrators and more.  Many are from poor families.   CHI provides high school and university students with scholarships so they can continue their studies at the private Yacoobi high schools or at university.  The goal is to improve the standing of women and girls in society and to close the gap in gender equality.</narrative>
  </description>
